{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892506650,"sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7117aa0015Qi1mHhb8A7e5L","messageID":"msg_d7b710d52001VW9GrJO5skOfCY","sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b57473baf6bc413d9f2ea7a9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n2: \n3: - **Module**: docs\n4: - **Language**: TypeScript\n5: - **Size**: M\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Initialize a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project.\n\n(End of file - total 9 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n- **Module**: docs\n- **Language**: TypeScript\n- **Size**: M\n\n## Summary\n\nInitialize a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/spec.md","time":{"start":1775892506624,"end":1775892506648}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892506657,"sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","part":{"id":"prt_d7b71225a001iHIisHBvNNuk5N","messageID":"msg_d7b710d52001VW9GrJO5skOfCY","sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e6314b38e06d4273b97d9742","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `root`  \n6: **Language:** Makefile  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Makefile target system for Docker image build, push, validate, test lifecycle management\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** design.md, deployment/docker/delta-spec.md (AR-032)\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-033.1: Build Targets (docker-build-*)\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building Docker images for all components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod).\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build all images\n21: - **GIVEN** Makefile exists with `docker-build-all` target\n22: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` is executed\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL build all three images (workloadmanager, router, picod) sequentially\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n26: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile` exists\n27: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` is executed\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Build Router image\n31: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router` exists\n32: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` is executed\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Build Picod image\n36: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists\n37: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` is executed\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Default registry configuration\n41: - **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_REGISTRY` variable is set\n42: - **WHEN** any build target runs\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL use default registry `ghcr.io/volcano-sh`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Custom registry override\n46: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n47: - **WHEN** build target runs\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom registry in image name\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Default tag configuration\n51: - **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_TAG` variable is set\n52: - **WHEN** any build target runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL use default tag `latest`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Custom tag override\n56: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0` is set\n57: - **WHEN** build target runs\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom tag in image name\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-033.2: Push Targets (docker-push-*)\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for pushing Docker images to container registry.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Push all images\n67: - **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-push-all` target exists\n68: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-all` is executed\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three images to registry\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n72: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n73: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager` is executed\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Push Router image\n77: - **GIVEN** router image is built\n78: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-router` is executed\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Push Picod image\n82: - **GIVEN** picod image is built\n83: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-picod` is executed\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Push with custom registry\n87: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n88: - **WHEN** push target runs\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL push to specified custom registry\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### REQ-033.3: Kind Load Targets (kind-load-*)\n94: \n95: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for loading Docker images to local Kind Kubernetes cluster.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Load all images to Kind\n98: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and images are built\n99: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL load all three images to Kind cluster\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Load Workload Manager image to Kind\n103: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and workloadmanager image is built\n104: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-workloadmanager` is executed\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL load workloadmanager image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Load Router image to Kind\n108: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and router image is built\n109: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-router` is executed\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL load router image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Load Picod image to Kind\n113: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and picod image is built\n114: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-picod` is executed\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL load picod image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Kind not installed\n118: - **GIVEN** Kind is not installed on the system\n119: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about Kind not found\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### REQ-033.4: Multi-architecture Build Targets (docker-buildx-*)\n125: \n126: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building multi-architecture Docker images using Docker Buildx.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Build all multi-arch images\n129: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available and `docker-buildx-all` target exists\n130: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL build multi-arch images for all three components\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager multi-arch image\n134: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n135: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-workloadmanager` is executed\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build Router multi-arch image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n140: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-router` is executed\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Build Picod multi-arch image\n144: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n145: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-picod` is executed\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Buildx not available\n149: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is not installed\n150: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about buildx not found\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### REQ-033.5: Validate Targets (docker-validate-*)\n156: \n157: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for validating Docker images against quality standards (size, layers, security, ports).\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Validate all images\n160: - **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-validate` target exists\n161: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL run validation script against all three images\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Validate Workload Manager image\n165: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n166: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-workloadmanager` is executed\n167: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Validate Router image\n170: - **GIVEN** router image is built\n171: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-router` is executed\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Validate Picod image\n175: - **GIVEN** picod image is built\n176: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-picod` is executed\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Validation script not found\n180: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` does not exist\n181: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### REQ-033.6: Test Targets (docker-test-*)\n187: \n188: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for running Docker build and runtime tests.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Run all Docker tests\n191: - **GIVEN** `docker-test` target exists\n192: - **WHEN** `make docker-test` is executed\n193: - **THEN** it SHALL run both `docker-test-build` and `docker-test-runtime`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Run build tests\n196: - **GIVEN** `docker-test-build` target exists\n197: - **WHEN** `make docker-test-build` is executed\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Run runtime tests\n201: - **GIVEN** `docker-test-runtime` target exists\n202: - **WHEN** `make docker-test-runtime` is executed\n203: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Test script not found\n206: - **GIVEN** test script does not exist\n207: - **WHEN** corresponding test target is executed\n208: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ### REQ-033.7: Clean Target (docker-clean)\n213: \n214: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make target for cleaning up local Docker images.\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Clean all local images\n217: - **GIVEN** local images exist and `docker-clean` target exists\n218: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL remove all local tags for workloadmanager, router, and picod images\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Clean with missing images\n222: - **GIVEN** some images do not exist locally\n223: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail and SHALL silently skip missing images\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### REQ-033.8: Help Target (help)\n229: \n230: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `help` target that prints available Make targets and their descriptions.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Display help information\n233: - **GIVEN** `help` target exists in Makefile\n234: - **WHEN** `make help` is executed\n235: - **THEN** it SHALL print all available targets grouped by category (build, push, kind, buildx, test, validate, clean)\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Display variable values\n238: - **GIVEN** `help` target is executed\n239: - **WHEN** help output is printed\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL show current values of `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, and `COMMIT_SHA`\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### REQ-033.9: Validation Script (validate.sh)\n245: \n246: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` script for validating Docker images.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Validate image size\n249: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n250: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs against the image\n251: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image size is under 50MB\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Validate layer count\n254: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n255: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n256: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image has 5 or fewer layers\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Validate non-root user\n259: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n260: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n261: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image specifies non-root user (not root)\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Validate port exposure\n264: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n265: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n266: - **THEN** it SHALL check that port 8080 is exposed\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Validate health check\n269: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n270: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL check that HEALTHCHECK instruction is configured\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Image not found\n274: - **GIVEN** the specified image does not exist\n275: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` is executed\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL exit with error code and message \"Image not found\"\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n279: - **GIVEN** `validate.sh` file exists\n280: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n281: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ### REQ-033.10: Build Test Script (build_test.sh)\n286: \n287: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` script for testing Docker build process.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Check Dockerfile existence\n290: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n291: - **WHEN** it checks for Dockerfiles\n292: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.router`, and `Dockerfile.picod` exist\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Check Makefile targets\n295: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n296: - **WHEN** it checks Makefile targets\n297: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `docker-build-all` target is available\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Check Docker daemon\n300: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n301: - **WHEN** it checks Docker daemon\n302: - **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker daemon is running\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Check buildx availability\n305: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n306: - **WHEN** it checks buildx\n307: - **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker buildx is available (optional, non-fatal)\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n310: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` file exists\n311: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n312: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ### REQ-033.11: Runtime Test Script (runtime_test.sh)\n317: \n318: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` script for testing Docker container runtime behavior.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Test container startup\n321: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs and test image exists\n322: - **WHEN** it attempts container startup\n323: - **THEN** it SHALL verify container starts successfully\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Test health check configuration\n326: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n327: - **WHEN** it checks health check\n328: - **THEN** it SHALL verify HEALTHCHECK is configured in image\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Test port exposure\n331: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n332: - **WHEN** it checks ports\n333: - **THEN** it SHALL verify port 8080 is exposed\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Test non-root user\n336: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n337: - **WHEN** it checks user configuration\n338: - **THEN** it SHALL verify container runs as non-root user\n339: \n340: #### Scenario: Image not available\n341: - **GIVEN** test image does not exist locally\n342: - **WHEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n343: - **THEN** it SHALL gracefully skip tests with warning messages (non-fatal)\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n346: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` file exists\n347: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n348: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ### REQ-033.12: Version and Commit Variables\n353: \n354: **Requirement:** The system SHALL automatically derive VERSION and COMMIT_SHA from git for use in image tagging.\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Derive VERSION from git tags\n357: - **GIVEN** repository has git tags\n358: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL use `git describe --tags --always --dirty` output\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Fallback VERSION for no tags\n362: - **GIVEN** repository has no git tags\n363: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n364: - **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `dev`\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Derive COMMIT_SHA from git\n367: - **GIVEN** repository is a valid git repo\n368: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n369: - **THEN** it SHALL use `git rev-parse --short HEAD` output\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Fallback COMMIT_SHA for non-git\n372: - **GIVEN** not in a git repository\n373: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n374: - **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `unknown`\n375: \n376: #### Scenario: Override VERSION from environment\n377: - **GIVEN** `VERSION` environment variable is set\n378: - **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n379: - **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Override COMMIT_SHA from environment\n382: - **GIVEN** `COMMIT_SHA` environment variable is set\n383: - **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n384: - **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ### REQ-033.13: Image Name Configuration\n389: \n390: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide consistent image naming convention for all components.\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image name\n393: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n394: - **WHEN** `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n395: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager`\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Router image name\n398: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n399: - **WHEN** `ROUTER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n400: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router`\n401: \n402: #### Scenario: Picod image name\n403: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n404: - **WHEN** `PICOD_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n405: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod`\n406: \n407: ---\n408: \n409: ### REQ-033.14: PHONY Target Declarations\n410: \n411: **Requirement:** The system SHALL declare all Make targets as `.PHONY` to prevent conflicts with files of the same name.\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: All targets declared as PHONY\n414: - **GIVEN** Makefile exists\n415: - **WHEN** `.PHONY` declarations are inspected\n416: - **THEN** all targets (docker-build-*, docker-push-*, kind-load-*, docker-buildx-*, docker-validate-*, docker-test-*, docker-clean, help) SHALL be declared as `.PHONY`\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ### REQ-033.15: Error Handling\n421: \n422: **Requirement:** The system SHALL handle errors gracefully in Make targets and scripts.\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Docker command failure\n425: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n426: - **WHEN** a build target is executed\n427: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with clear error message about Docker not being available\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: Clean target with missing images\n430: - **GIVEN** some images do not exist\n431: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` runs\n432: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail (uses `-` prefix to ignore errors)\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n435: - **GIVEN** Dockerfile does not exist\n436: - **WHEN** build target runs\n437: - **THEN** Docker build command SHALL fail with appropriate error\n438: \n439: ---\n440: \n441: ## Data Types\n442: \n443: ```makefile\n444: # Makefile variables\n445: DOCKER_REGISTRY := ghcr.io/volcano-sh     # Default container registry\n446: DOCKER_TAG := latest                       # Default image tag\n447: VERSION := $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n448: COMMIT_SHA := $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n449: \n450: # Image names (constructed)\n451: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n452: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n453: PICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## File Structure\n459: \n460: ```\n461: project-root/\n462: ├── Makefile                              # Main Makefile with all targets\n463: ├── deployment/\n464: │   └── docker/\n465: │       ├── Dockerfile                    # Workload Manager Dockerfile (AR-032)\n466: │       ├── Dockerfile.router             # Router Dockerfile (AR-032)\n467: │       ├── Dockerfile.picod              # Picod Dockerfile (AR-032)\n468: │       └── test/\n469: │           ├── validate.sh               # Image validation script (new)\n470: │           ├── build_test.sh             # Build test script (new)\n471: │           └── runtime_test.sh           # Runtime test script (new)\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Make Targets\n477: \n478: | Target | Category | Description |\n479: |--------|----------|-------------|\n480: | `docker-build-all` | Build | Build all three Docker images |\n481: | `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build | Build Workload Manager image |\n482: | `docker-build-router` | Build | Build Router image |\n483: | `docker-build-picod` | Build | Build Picod image |\n484: | `docker-push-all` | Push | Push all images to registry |\n485: | `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push | Push Workload Manager image |\n486: | `docker-push-router` | Push | Push Router image |\n487: | `docker-push-picod` | Push | Push Picod image |\n488: | `kind-load-all` | Kind | Load all images to Kind cluster |\n489: | `kind-load-workloadmanager` | Kind | Load Workload Manager image to Kind |\n490: | `kind-load-router` | Kind | Load Router image to Kind |\n491: | `kind-load-picod` | Kind | Load Picod image to Kind |\n492: | `docker-buildx-all` | Buildx | Build multi-arch images (amd64, arm64) |\n493: | `docker-buildx-workloadmanager` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Workload Manager |\n494: | `docker-buildx-router` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Router |\n495: | `docker-buildx-picod` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Picod |\n496: | `docker-validate` | Validate | Validate all images |\n497: | `docker-validate-workloadmanager` | Validate | Validate Workload Manager image |\n498: | `docker-validate-router` | Validate | Validate Router image |\n499: | `docker-validate-picod` | Validate | Validate Picod image |\n500: | `docker-test` | Test | Run all Docker tests |\n501: | `docker-test-build` | Test | Run build tests |\n502: | `docker-test-runtime` | Test | Run runtime tests |\n503: | `docker-clean` | Clean | Clean up local images |\n504: | `help` | Help | Print available targets and variables |\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Environment Variables\n509: \n510: | Variable | Purpose | Default | Overridable |\n511: |----------|---------|---------|-------------|\n512: | `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | Container registry URL | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Yes |\n513: | `DOCKER_TAG` | Default image tag | `latest` | Yes |\n514: | `VERSION` | Git-derived version | `git describe` or `dev` | Yes |\n515: | `COMMIT_SHA` | Git commit short hash | `git rev-parse` or `unknown` | Yes |\n516: | `TEST_IMAGE` | Test image for runtime tests | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest` | Yes |\n517: \n518: ---\n519: \n520: ## Script Interfaces\n521: \n522: ### validate.sh\n523: \n524: ```bash\n525: # Usage\n526: ./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh <image-name>\n527: \n528: # Exit codes\n529: 0 - All validations passed\n530: 1 - Validation failed or image not found\n531: \n532: # Validations performed\n533: - Image existence check\n534: - Image size < 50MB\n535: - Layer count <= 5\n536: - Non-root user specified\n537: - Port 8080 exposed\n538: - Health check configured\n539: ```\n540: \n541: ### build_test.sh\n542: \n543: ```bash\n544: # Usage\n545: ./deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh\n546: \n547: # Exit codes\n548: 0 - All build tests passed\n549: 1 - Test failed\n550: \n551: # Tests performed\n552: - Dockerfile existence check (3 files)\n553: - Makefile target availability\n554: - Docker daemon running check\n555: - Docker buildx availability (optional)\n556: ```\n557: \n558: ### runtime_test.sh\n559: \n560: ```bash\n561: # Usage\n562: ./deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh\n563: \n564: # Exit codes\n565: 0 - All runtime tests completed\n566: 1 - Critical test failed\n567: \n568: # Tests performed\n569: - Container startup test\n570: - Health check configuration check\n571: - Port exposure check\n572: - Non-root user check\n573: ```\n574: \n575: ---\n576: \n577: ## Acceptance Checklist\n578: \n579: - [ ] `Makefile` — Contains all build, push, kind, buildx, validate, test, clean, and help targets\n580: - [ ] `Makefile` — All targets declared as `.PHONY`\n581: - [ ] `Makefile` — Variables `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` defined\n582: - [ ] `Makefile` — Image name variables for all three components\n583: - [ ] `make help` — Prints all available targets and current variable values\n584: - [ ] `make docker-build-all` — Builds all three images successfully\n585: - [ ] `make docker-push-all` — Pushes all images (with valid credentials)\n586: - [ ] `make kind-load-all` — Loads images to Kind cluster (with Kind installed)\n587: - [ ] `make docker-buildx-all` — Builds multi-arch images (with buildx available)\n588: - [ ] `make docker-validate` — Validates all images\n589: - [ ] `make docker-test` — Runs all tests\n590: - [ ] `make docker-clean` — Cleans up local images\n591: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` — Exists and is executable\n592: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n593: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n594: - [ ] `validate.sh` — Checks image size, layers, user, ports, healthcheck\n595: - [ ] `build_test.sh` — Checks Dockerfiles, Makefile targets, Docker daemon\n596: - [ ] `runtime_test.sh` — Tests container runtime behavior\n597: - [ ] VERSION variable — Derived from git tags with fallback to `dev`\n598: - [ ] COMMIT_SHA variable — Derived from git with fallback to `unknown`\n599: - [ ] Variables overridable — Can be set from environment or command line\n600: - [ ] Error handling — Clean target ignores missing images gracefully\n601: \n602: ---\n603: \n604: ## Open Questions\n605: \n606: 1. Should Windows support be added via PowerShell scripts or WSL-only?\n607: 2. Should cosign image signing be integrated into push targets?\n608: 3. Should remote Docker daemon support (DOCKER_HOST) be explicitly documented?\n609: 4. Should additional validation checks be added (e.g., vulnerability scanning with Trivy)?\n610: 5. Should a `make ci` target be added that chains test → build → validate?\n\n(End of file - total 610 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `root`  \n**Language:** Makefile  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Makefile target system for Docker image build, push, validate, test lifecycle management\n\n**Base Specs:** design.md, deployment/docker/delta-spec.md (AR-032)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-033.1: Build Targets (docker-build-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building Docker images for all components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod).\n\n#### Scenario: Build all images","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775892506630,"end":1775892506655}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892506661,"sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","part":{"id":"prt_d7b711cba001NSFIQzxvp3LgmV","messageID":"msg_d7b710d52001VW9GrJO5skOfCY","sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_17078bff527d48c1a87f888f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 Workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `.github/workflows`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation (build, lint, test, e2e, codegen, copyright, codespell, release, approval)\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** ci-cd/design.md, ci-cd/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-034.1: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: PR triggers workflow\n21: - **GIVEN** a pull request is opened or updated targeting `main` or `release-*`\n22: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n23: - **THEN** the \"Agentcube CI Workflow\" SHALL be triggered\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Checkout repository\n26: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n27: - **WHEN** the job starts\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository code\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Setup Docker Buildx\n31: - **GIVEN** repository is checked out\n32: - **WHEN** job continues\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Docker Buildx\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Verify Docker availability\n36: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is set up\n37: - **WHEN** job continues\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `docker` and `buildx` versions\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Execute docker-build\n41: - **GIVEN** Docker is available\n42: - **WHEN** build step runs\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-build`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### REQ-034.2: E2E Tests Workflow (e2e.yml)\n48: \n49: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs end-to-end tests on Kind Kubernetes cluster for pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: PR triggers e2e workflow\n52: - **GIVEN** a pull request is opened or updated targeting `main` or `release-*`\n53: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n54: - **THEN** the \"Agentcube E2E Tests\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Setup Go environment\n57: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n58: - **WHEN** the job starts\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.23\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Install Kind cluster\n62: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n63: - **WHEN** Kind action runs\n64: - **THEN** it SHALL install Kind v0.30.0 with `install_only: true` and cluster name `agentcube-e2e`\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Set artifacts path\n67: - **GIVEN** Kind is installed\n68: - **WHEN** environment is configured\n69: - **THEN** `ARTIFACTS_PATH` SHALL be set to `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Run e2e tests\n72: - **GIVEN** cluster is ready\n73: - **WHEN** test step runs\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make e2e`\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Upload failure logs\n77: - **GIVEN** e2e tests fail\n78: - **WHEN** failure occurs\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL upload `e2e-logs/` directory as artifact\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Clean up cluster\n82: - **GIVEN** tests complete (pass or fail)\n83: - **WHEN** job finishes\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL always run `make e2e-clean`\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### REQ-034.3: Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n89: \n90: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs `golangci-lint` when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: PR triggers lint workflow\n93: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n94: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n95: - **THEN** the \"Lint\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Path filter for Go files\n98: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n99: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL match `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Setup Go for linting\n103: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n104: - **WHEN** lint job continues\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Run golangci-lint\n108: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n109: - **WHEN** lint step runs\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make lint`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: No Go changes\n113: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no Go-related changes\n114: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n115: - **THEN** lint step SHALL be skipped\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### REQ-034.4: Python SDK Tests Workflow (python-sdk-tests.yml)\n120: \n121: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs pytest for the Python SDK when `sdk-python/**` paths change.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: PR triggers Python SDK workflow\n124: - **GIVEN** a pull request or merge_group event occurs\n125: - **WHEN** the event targets the repository\n126: - **THEN** the \"Python SDK Tests\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Path filter for SDK files\n129: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n130: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL match `sdk-python/**`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Setup Python environment\n134: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates SDK changes\n135: - **WHEN** job continues\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Python 3.12 with working directory `sdk-python`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Install pytest\n139: - **GIVEN** Python is ready\n140: - **WHEN** dependency step runs\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install pytest`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Install SDK in editable mode\n144: - **GIVEN** pytest is installed\n145: - **WHEN** install step runs\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install -e .`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Run pytest\n149: - **GIVEN** SDK is installed\n150: - **WHEN** test step runs\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: No SDK changes\n154: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no SDK changes\n155: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n156: - **THEN** test steps SHALL be skipped\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### REQ-034.5: Python Lint Workflow (python-lint.yml)\n161: \n162: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs Ruff linting when Python-related paths change.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: PR triggers Python lint workflow\n165: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n166: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n167: - **THEN** the \"Python Lint\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Path filter for Python files\n170: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n171: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL match `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file itself\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Setup Python for linting\n175: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n176: - **WHEN** job continues\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Python 3.10\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Install Ruff\n180: - **GIVEN** Python is ready\n181: - **WHEN** dependency step runs\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install ruff`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Run Ruff check\n185: - **GIVEN** Ruff is installed\n186: - **WHEN** lint step runs\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: No Python changes\n190: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no Python-related changes\n191: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n192: - **THEN** lint steps SHALL be skipped\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ### REQ-034.6: Test Coverage Workflow (test-coverage.yml)\n197: \n198: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs race-enabled Go tests with coverage reporting on `pkg/...` for pull requests, merge groups, or workflow calls.\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Multiple triggers for coverage\n201: - **GIVEN** a `pull_request`, `merge_group`, or `workflow_call` event occurs\n202: - **WHEN** the event targets the repository\n203: - **THEN** the \"Test Coverage\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Path filter for coverage\n206: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n207: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n208: - **THEN** it SHALL match `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Free disk space\n211: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n212: - **WHEN** job starts\n213: - **THEN** it SHALL free disk space on the runner\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Setup Go for tests\n216: - **GIVEN** disk space is ready\n217: - **WHEN** job continues\n218: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Run Go tests with coverage\n221: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n222: - **WHEN** test step runs\n223: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Upload coverage to Codecov\n226: - **GIVEN** coverage report is generated\n227: - **WHEN** upload step runs\n228: - **THEN** it SHALL upload `coverage.out` to Codecov (using `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` if available)\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Upload coverage artifact\n231: - **GIVEN** coverage report exists\n232: - **WHEN** artifact step runs\n233: - **THEN** it SHALL upload `go-coverage` artifact\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Write to step summary\n236: - **GIVEN** tests complete\n237: - **WHEN** summary step runs\n238: - **THEN** it SHALL write coverage results to GitHub step summary\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### REQ-034.7: Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n243: \n244: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that verifies generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: PR triggers codegen workflow\n247: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n248: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n249: - **THEN** the \"Codegen Check\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Path filter for codegen\n252: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n253: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n254: - **THEN** it SHALL match `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Setup Go for codegen\n257: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n258: - **WHEN** job continues\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24.4\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Run gen-check\n262: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n263: - **WHEN** check step runs\n264: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-check` (runs `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code`)\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Generated code out of date\n267: - **GIVEN** `make gen-all` produces changes\n268: - **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` runs\n269: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail indicating generated code is stale\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: No codegen-related changes\n272: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no relevant changes\n273: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n274: - **THEN** check steps SHALL be skipped\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ### REQ-034.8: Copyright Check Workflow (copyright-check.yml)\n279: \n280: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that ensures `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: PR triggers copyright workflow\n283: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n284: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n285: - **THEN** the \"Copyright Check\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Path filter for copyright\n288: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n289: - **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL match all files excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Install moreutils\n293: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n294: - **WHEN** job starts\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` package (for `sponge` command)\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: Run gen-copyright\n298: - **GIVEN** moreutils is installed\n299: - **WHEN** generate step runs\n300: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-copyright`\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Verify no diff\n303: - **GIVEN** copyright headers are generated\n304: - **WHEN** diff step runs\n305: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `git diff --exit-code`\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Copyright headers missing\n308: - **GIVEN** files lack proper copyright headers\n309: - **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` runs\n310: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail indicating missing copyright headers\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: No copyright-relevant changes\n313: - **GIVEN** path filter indicates no relevant changes\n314: - **WHEN** workflow runs\n315: - **THEN** check steps SHALL be skipped\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### REQ-034.9: Codespell Workflow (codespell.yml)\n320: \n321: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs codespell spell-checking on pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: PR triggers codespell workflow\n324: - **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n325: - **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n326: - **THEN** the \"Codespell\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: Backup problematic files\n329: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n330: - **WHEN** job starts\n331: - **THEN** it SHALL backup and remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json` at repo root and nested copies\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: Install codespell\n334: - **GIVEN** files are backed up\n335: - **WHEN** dependency step runs\n336: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install codespell`\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Run codespell\n339: - **GIVEN** codespell is installed\n340: - **WHEN** spell check step runs\n341: - **THEN** it SHALL run `codespell --check-filenames --skip <globs> --ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn .`\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Restore backed-up files\n344: - **GIVEN** codespell completes\n345: - **WHEN** cleanup step runs\n346: - **THEN** it SHALL restore all backed-up files\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Spelling errors found\n349: - **GIVEN** repository contains misspellings\n350: - **WHEN** codespell runs\n351: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail with list of misspelled words\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ### REQ-034.10: Build and Push Release Images Workflow (build-push-release.yml)\n356: \n357: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds and pushes multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and semantic version tags.\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: Push to main triggers workflow\n360: - **GIVEN** a push to `main` branch occurs\n361: - **WHEN** the push event completes\n362: - **THEN** the \"Build and Push Release Images\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: Tag push triggers workflow\n365: - **GIVEN** a push of tag matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*` occurs\n366: - **WHEN** the tag event completes\n367: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL be triggered\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Determine image tag from ref\n370: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n371: - **WHEN** `TAG` environment variable is evaluated\n372: - **THEN** it SHALL use `github.ref_name` if tag, otherwise `latest`\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: Setup Go for build\n375: - **GIVEN** workflow is triggered\n376: - **WHEN** job starts\n377: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24.4\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Setup Docker Buildx\n380: - **GIVEN** Go is ready\n381: - **WHEN** job continues\n382: - **THEN** it SHALL set up Docker Buildx\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: Login to GHCR\n385: - **GIVEN** Buildx is ready\n386: - **WHEN** login step runs\n387: - **THEN** it SHALL authenticate to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: Build and push workloadmanager\n390: - **GIVEN** registry login succeeds\n391: - **WHEN** build step runs\n392: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Build and push router\n395: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n396: - **WHEN** router build step runs\n397: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push-router` with appropriate image variables\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Build and push picod\n400: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n401: - **WHEN** picod build step runs\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with appropriate image variables\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Multi-architecture build\n405: - **GIVEN** buildx is available\n406: - **WHEN** build commands run\n407: - **THEN** images SHALL be built for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ### REQ-034.11: Dify Plugin Publish Workflow (dify-plugin-publish.yml)\n412: \n413: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that publishes the Dify plugin to the `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository when `dify-plugin/v*` tags are pushed.\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers workflow\n416: - **GIVEN** a push of tag matching `dify-plugin/v*` occurs\n417: - **WHEN** the tag event completes\n418: - **THEN** the \"Dify Plugin Publish\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Download dify-plugin CLI\n421: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n422: - **WHEN** setup step runs\n423: - **THEN** it SHALL download `dify-plugin` CLI version 0.0.6\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Install yq processor\n426: - **GIVEN** workflow continues\n427: - **WHEN** tooling step runs\n428: - **THEN** it SHALL install `yq` YAML processor\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Read manifest\n431: - **GIVEN** tools are ready\n432: - **WHEN** manifest step runs\n433: - **THEN** it SHALL read `manifest.yaml` for plugin metadata\n434: \n435: #### Scenario: Package plugin\n436: - **GIVEN** manifest is parsed\n437: - **WHEN** packaging step runs\n438: - **THEN** it SHALL package the Dify plugin\n439: \n440: #### Scenario: Checkout plugins repository\n441: - **GIVEN** plugin is packaged\n442: - **WHEN** repository step runs\n443: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout `author/dify-plugins` using token authentication\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Move plugin to repository\n446: - **GIVEN** repository is checked out\n447: - **WHEN** file step runs\n448: - **THEN** it SHALL move `.difypkg` file to appropriate location\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: Create pull request\n451: - **GIVEN** plugin files are staged\n452: - **WHEN** PR step runs\n453: - **THEN** it SHALL create branch, commit, push, and create PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins` using `gh pr create` with `GH_TOKEN`\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ### REQ-034.12: Approve Workflows Workflow (workflows-approve.yml)\n458: \n459: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that optionally approves pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: PR target triggers approval workflow\n462: - **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event with types `labeled` or `synchronize` targets `main` or `release-**`\n463: - **WHEN** the event occurs\n464: - **THEN** the \"Approve Workflows\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: Check contributor PR history\n467: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n468: - **WHEN** github-script step runs\n469: - **THEN** it SHALL list contributor's PRs to determine if first-time\n470: \n471: #### Scenario: Check for ok-to-test label\n472: - **GIVEN** workflow is running\n473: - **WHEN** label check runs\n474: - **THEN** it SHALL check if PR has `ok-to-test` label\n475: \n476: #### Scenario: Approve for repeat contributor\n477: - **GIVEN** contributor has more than one PR\n478: - **WHEN** approval logic runs\n479: - **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs with `status: action_required` for the head SHA and approve each\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Approve for labeled PR\n482: - **GIVEN** PR has `ok-to-test` label\n483: - **WHEN** approval logic runs\n484: - **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs with `status: action_required` for the head SHA and approve each\n485: \n486: #### Scenario: Skip for first-time contributor\n487: - **GIVEN** contributor has only one PR and no `ok-to-test` label\n488: - **WHEN** approval logic runs\n489: - **THEN** no workflow runs SHALL be approved\n490: \n491: ---\n492: \n493: ## Data Types\n494: \n495: ```yaml\n496: # Workflow trigger types\n497: on:\n498:   pull_request:\n499:     branches: [main, release-*]\n500:   pull_request_target:\n501:     branches: [main, release-**]\n502:     types: [labeled, synchronize]\n503:   push:\n504:     branches: [main]\n505:     tags: ['v*.*.*', 'v*.*.*-*', 'dify-plugin/v*']\n506:   merge_group:\n507:   workflow_call:\n508: \n509: # Common job environment variables\n510: env:\n511:   TAG: ${{ github.ref_type == 'tag' && github.ref_name || 'latest' }}\n512:   IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n513:   ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n514: ```\n515: \n516: ---\n517: \n518: ## File Structure\n519: \n520: ```\n521: .github/\n522: └── workflows/\n523:     ├── main.yml                      # Agentcube CI Workflow (REQ-034.1)\n524:     ├── e2e.yml                       # Agentcube E2E Tests (REQ-034.2)\n525:     ├── lint.yml                      # Lint (REQ-034.3)\n526:     ├── python-sdk-tests.yml          # Python SDK Tests (REQ-034.4)\n527:     ├── python-lint.yml               # Python Lint (REQ-034.5)\n528:     ├── test-coverage.yml             # Test Coverage (REQ-034.6)\n529:     ├── codegen-check.yml             # Codegen Check (REQ-034.7)\n530:     ├── copyright-check.yml           # Copyright Check (REQ-034.8)\n531:     ├── codespell.yml                 # Codespell (REQ-034.9)\n532:     ├── build-push-release.yml        # Build and Push Release Images (REQ-034.10)\n533:     ├── dify-plugin-publish.yml       # Dify Plugin Publish (REQ-034.11)\n534:     └── workflows-approve.yml         # Approve Workflows (REQ-034.12)\n535: ```\n536: \n537: ---\n538: \n539: ## Workflows Summary\n540: \n541: | Workflow | File | Triggers | Path Filters | Key Jobs |\n542: |----------|------|----------|--------------|----------|\n543: | Agentcube CI Workflow | main.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None | build |\n544: | Agentcube E2E Tests | e2e.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None | e2e-test |\n545: | Lint | lint.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Go files | golangci |\n546: | Python SDK Tests | python-sdk-tests.yml | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests |\n547: | Python Lint | python-lint.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Python files | python_lint |\n548: | Test Coverage | test-coverage.yml | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | All except media | coverage |\n549: | Codegen Check | codegen-check.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | API/hack/workflow/Makefile | codegen-check |\n550: | Copyright Check | copyright-check.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Code files only | build |\n551: | Codespell | codespell.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None (tree scan) | codespell |\n552: | Build and Push Release | build-push-release.yml | `push` → `main`, tags `v*` | None | build-and-push |\n553: | Dify Plugin Publish | dify-plugin-publish.yml | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | None | publish |\n554: | Approve Workflows | workflows-approve.yml | `pull_request_target` → `main` | None | approve |\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ## Secrets and Credentials\n559: \n560: | Secret | Purpose | Used By |\n561: |--------|---------|---------|\n562: | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` | Codecov coverage upload | test-coverage.yml (optional) |\n563: | `secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN` | GHCR registry login, cross-repo PR | build-push-release.yml, dify-plugin-publish.yml, workflows-approve.yml |\n564: | `secrets.PLUGIN_ACTION` | Dify plugin repository checkout and PR | dify-plugin-publish.yml |\n565: \n566: ---\n567: \n568: ## Acceptance Checklist\n569: \n570: - [ ] `main.yml` — Triggers on PR to `main`/`release-*`, runs `make docker-build`\n571: - [ ] `e2e.yml` — Triggers on PR, sets up Kind v0.30.0, runs `make e2e`, uploads logs on failure, cleans up\n572: - [ ] `lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Go files, runs `make lint` with Go 1.24\n573: - [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` — Path-filtered for `sdk-python/**`, runs pytest with Python 3.12\n574: - [ ] `python-lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Python files, runs Ruff with Python 3.10\n575: - [ ] `test-coverage.yml` — Runs `go test -race` with coverage, uploads to Codecov\n576: - [ ] `codegen-check.yml` — Path-filtered, runs `make gen-check` with Go 1.24.4\n577: - [ ] `copyright-check.yml` — Installs moreutils, runs `make gen-copyright`, checks diff\n578: - [ ] `codespell.yml` — Backups files, runs codespell with ignore list, restores files\n579: - [ ] `build-push-release.yml` — Triggers on push to `main`/tags, builds multi-arch, pushes to GHCR\n580: - [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` — Triggers on `dify-plugin/v*` tags, creates PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n581: - [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` — Approves workflows for repeat contributors or `ok-to-test` labeled PRs\n582: - [ ] All workflows — Use appropriate Go/Python versions as specified\n583: - [ ] All workflows — Have correct path filters configured\n584: - [ ] All workflows — Handle skip conditions correctly when paths don't match\n585: - [ ] Secrets — CODECOV_TOKEN is optional in test-coverage.yml\n586: - [ ] Secrets — GITHUB_TOKEN used for GHCR login and cross-repo operations\n587: - [ ] E2E workflow — Uses Kind action with `install_only: true`\n588: - [ ] Release workflow — Correctly determines TAG from ref type\n589: \n590: ---\n591: \n592: ## Open Questions\n593: \n594: 1. Should Windows CI runners be added for cross-platform validation?\n595: 2. Should SLSA/SBOM generation be integrated into the release workflow?\n596: 3. Should Dependabot be configured alongside these workflows?\n597: 4. Should workflow concurrency limits be added to prevent queue buildup?\n598: 5. Should additional notification hooks (Slack, Discord) be added for release failures?\n\n(End of file - total 598 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 Workflows)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `.github/workflows`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation (build, lint, test, e2e, codegen, copyright, codespell, release, approval)\n\n**Base Specs:** ci-cd/design.md, ci-cd/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-034.1: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers workflow","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775892506628,"end":1775892506658}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775892506686,"sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","part":{"id":"prt_d7b712825001T5uZ92fqRF5XWZ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b710d52001VW9GrJO5skOfCY","sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":17906,"input":6,"output":268,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":2154,"read":15478}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775892510378,"sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7136a8001zV9Zi5Ev6IsV0o","messageID":"msg_d7b7128540019Cu3AmNv4m9MZ5","sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892575687,"sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","part":{"id":"prt_d7b713eaf0013wxGr7lZuudDK7","messageID":"msg_d7b7128540019Cu3AmNv4m9MZ5","sessionID":"ses_2848f0890ffeClNkhobPSdDw09","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_d8398737af1f482c81d6ee0c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-042: Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docs`  \n**Language:** TypeScript  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Docusaurus-based documentation site initialization for agentcube project\n\n**Base Specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-042.1: Docusaurus Project Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a Docusaurus v3 project initialized in the `docs/` directory.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize Docusaurus project\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n- **WHEN** the documentation site is initialized\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a Docusaurus v3 project in the `docs/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: TypeScript configuration\n- **GIVEN** Docusaurus is initialized\n- **WHEN** project is set up\n- **THEN** it SHALL use TypeScript for configuration files (`docusaurus.config.ts`)\n\n#### Scenario: Package manager selection\n- **GIVEN** Docusaurus CLI runs\n- **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the project's existing package manager (npm/pnpm/yarn)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.2: Docusaurus Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docusaurus.config.ts` configuration file with agentcube branding and settings.\n\n#### Scenario: Site title configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `title` SHALL be set to \"agentcube\"\n\n#### Scenario: Site tagline configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `tagline` SHALL describe agentcube's purpose\n\n#### Scenario: Site URL configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `url` SHALL be set to project's documentation URL\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `baseUrl` SHALL be set to `/agentcube/`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment organization\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `organizationName` SHALL be set to appropriate GitHub org\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment project name\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `projectName` SHALL be set to \"agentcube\"\n\n#### Scenario: Theme configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL configure prism theme for code highlighting\n\n#### Scenario: Navigation bar configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `navbar` SHALL include links to docs, GitHub, and other sections\n\n#### Scenario: Footer configuration\n- **GIVEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `footer` SHALL include copyright and relevant links\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.3: Documentation Content Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a documentation directory structure with initial content.\n\n#### Scenario: Docs directory exists\n- **GIVEN** Docusaurus project is initialized\n- **WHEN** file structure is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/` directory SHALL exist for documentation markdown files\n\n#### Scenario: Introductory documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** initial content is created\n- **THEN** `docs/intro.md` SHALL provide project introduction\n\n#### Scenario: Getting started documentation\n- **GIVEN** `docs/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** initial content is created\n- **THEN** `docs/getting-started.md` SHALL provide setup instructions\n\n#### Scenario: Docs sidebar configuration\n- **GIVEN** Docusaurus is configured\n- **WHEN** sidebar is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL define a sidebar with intro and getting-started sections\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.4: Static Assets\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `static/` directory for static assets with branding.\n\n#### Scenario: Static directory exists\n- **GIVEN** Docusaurus project is initialized\n- **WHEN** file structure is inspected\n- **THEN** `static/` directory SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: Favicon configuration\n- **GIVEN** `static/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** assets are added\n- **THEN** `static/favicon.ico` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: Logo asset\n- **GIVEN** `static/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** branding assets are added\n- **THEN** `static/img/logo.svg` or `static/img/logo.png` SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: Robots.txt\n- **GIVEN** `static/` directory exists\n- **WHEN** SEO files are added\n- **THEN** `static/robots.txt` SHALL be present\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.5: NPM Scripts\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide NPM scripts in `docs/package.json` for common Docusaurus operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Start script\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n- **THEN** `start` script SHALL run Docusaurus development server\n\n#### Scenario: Build script\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n- **THEN** `build` script SHALL generate production build\n\n#### Scenario: Serve script\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n- **THEN** `serve` script SHALL serve production build locally\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy script\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** scripts are inspected\n- **THEN** `deploy` script SHALL deploy to GitHub Pages\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.6: Dependencies\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL specify required Docusaurus dependencies in `package.json`.\n\n#### Scenario: Core Docusaurus dependency\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n- **THEN** `@docusaurus/core` SHALL be listed as dependency (v3.x)\n\n#### Scenario: Preset Classic\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n- **THEN** `@docusaurus/preset-classic` SHALL be listed as dependency\n\n#### Scenario: TypeScript support\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n- **THEN** `@docusaurus/module-type-aliases` and `@docusaurus/tsconfig` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: React dependencies\n- **GIVEN** `docs/package.json` exists\n- **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n- **THEN** `react` and `react-dom` SHALL be listed as dependencies\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.7: TypeScript Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide TypeScript configuration for the docs project.\n\n#### Scenario: TSConfig file exists\n- **GIVEN** Docusaurus project is initialized\n- **WHEN** configuration is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: Docusaurus TSConfig extends\n- **GIVEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL extend `@docusaurus/tsconfig`\n\n#### Scenario: Module resolution\n- **GIVEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` exists\n- **WHEN** configuration is evaluated\n- **THEN** `moduleResolution` SHALL be set to `bundler` or `node`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.8: Git Ignore Configuration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `.gitignore` for the docs directory.\n\n#### Scenario: Build output ignored\n- **GIVEN** `docs/.gitignore` exists\n- **WHEN** gitignore is inspected\n- **THEN** `build/` directory SHALL be ignored\n\n#### Scenario: Node modules ignored\n- **GIVEN** `docs/.gitignore` exists\n- **WHEN** gitignore is inspected\n- **THEN** `node_modules/` SHALL be ignored\n\n#### Scenario: Docusaurus cache ignored\n- **GIVEN** `docs/.gitignore` exists\n- **WHEN** gitignore is inspected\n- **THEN** `.docusaurus/` SHALL be ignored\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.9: Development Server\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL support running Docusaurus development server for local preview.\n\n#### Scenario: Start development server\n- **GIVEN** dependencies are installed\n- **WHEN** `npm start` (or equivalent) is executed in `docs/`\n- **THEN** Docusaurus dev server SHALL start on `localhost:3000`\n\n#### Scenario: Hot reload\n- **GIVEN** dev server is running\n- **WHEN** documentation markdown files are modified\n- **THEN** changes SHALL be reflected without manual refresh\n\n#### Scenario: Build without errors\n- **GIVEN** documentation content exists\n- **WHEN** `npm run build` is executed\n- **THEN** build SHALL complete without errors\n\n---\n\n### REQ-042.10: README Documentation\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docs/README.md` with instructions for working with the documentation site.\n\n#### Scenario: README exists\n- **GIVEN** docs directory is initialized\n- **WHEN** file structure is inspected\n- **THEN** `docs/README.md` SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: Quick start instructions\n- **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include commands to start dev server\n\n#### Scenario: Build instructions\n- **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include commands to build production site\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment instructions\n- **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n- **WHEN** content is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include instructions for deploying to GitHub Pages\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```typescript\n// docusaurus.config.ts structure\ninterface Config {\n  title: string;\n  tagline: string;\n  url: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  organizationName: string;\n  projectName: string;\n  presets: [\n    '@docusaurus/preset-classic',\n    {\n      docs: DocsOptions;\n      blog: false;\n      theme: ThemeOptions;\n    }\n  ];\n}\n```\n\n```json\n// package.json structure\n{\n  \"name\": \"agentcube-docs\",\n  \"version\": \"0.0.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n    \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n    \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n    \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"react\": \"^18.0.0\",\n    \"react-dom\": \"^18.0.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/tsconfig\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"~5.2.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── docs/\n│   ├── .gitignore                    # Git ignore for build artifacts\n│   ├── README.md                     # Documentation for working with docs\n│   ├── package.json                  # NPM dependencies and scripts\n│   ├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript configuration\n│   ├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus site configuration\n│   ├── sidebars.ts                   # Documentation sidebar configuration\n│   ├── docs/\n│   │   ├── intro.md                  # Introduction documentation\n│   │   └── getting-started.md        # Getting started guide\n│   └── static/\n│       ├── favicon.ico               # Site favicon\n│       ├── robots.txt                # SEO robots file\n│       └── img/\n│           └── logo.svg              # Project logo\n```\n\n---\n\n## NPM Scripts\n\n| Script | Command | Description |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| `start` | `docusaurus start` | Start development server at localhost:3000 |\n| `build` | `docusaurus build` | Generate static build into `build/` |\n| `serve` | `docusaurus serve` | Serve production build locally |\n| `deploy` | `docusaurus deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Options\n\n| Option | Purpose | Default | Overridable |\n|--------|---------|---------|-------------|\n| `title` | Site title | \"agentcube\" | Yes |\n| `tagline` | Site description | \"Documentation\" | Yes |\n| `url` | Site URL | \"https://your-docusaurus-site.github.io\" | Yes |\n| `baseUrl` | Base URL path | \"/agentcube/\" | Yes |\n| `organizationName` | GitHub org | \"volcano-sh\" | Yes |\n| `projectName` | GitHub repo | \"agentcube\" | Yes |\n| `deploymentBranch` | Deploy branch | \"gh-pages\" | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `docs/` — Directory exists with Docusaurus v3 project\n- [ ] `docs/package.json` — Contains required Docusaurus dependencies\n- [ ] `docs/package.json` — Contains `start`, `build`, `serve`, `deploy` scripts\n- [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — TypeScript configuration file exists\n- [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — Configured with agentcube branding\n- [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — URL and baseUrl properly set\n- [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — Navbar configured with links\n- [ ] `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` — Footer configured\n- [ ] `docs/tsconfig.json` — Extends @docusaurus/tsconfig\n- [ ] `docs/sidebars.ts` — Sidebar configuration exists\n- [ ] `docs/docs/intro.md` — Introduction documentation exists\n- [ ] `docs/docs/getting-started.md` — Getting started guide exists\n- [ ] `docs/static/` — Static assets directory exists\n- [ ] `docs/static/favicon.ico` — Favicon present\n- [ ] `docs/static/img/logo.svg` — Logo asset present\n- [ ] `docs/static/robots.txt` — SEO file present\n- [ ] `docs/.gitignore` — Ignores `build/`, `node_modules/`, `.docusaurus/`\n- [ ] `docs/README.md` — Instructions for working with docs\n- [ ] `npm start` — Development server starts successfully\n- [ ] `npm run build` — Production build completes without errors\n- [ ] Dependencies — All required packages installed\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should the documentation site be deployed as part of CI/CD automatically on merge to main?\n2. Should i18n (internationalization) be configured from the start?\n3. Should a blog section be enabled for release announcements?\n4. Should Algolia DocSearch be integrated for search functionality?\n5. Should custom CSS/theming be applied for agentcube branding?\n6. Should versioning (docs versioning) be enabled for multiple releases?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775892575666,"end":1775892575683}}}}
